article.story: DAYTON, Ohio -- — Javon Bennett had 19 points in Dayton's 91-67 win over Oakland on Wednesday night. Bennett added nine assists for the Flyers (9-2). Koby Brea scored 17 points while finishing 5 of 8 from 3-point range. Kobe Elvis had 14 points and was 4 of 14 shooting, including 3 for 9 from 3-point range, and went 3 for 3 from the line. The Flyers picked up their sixth straight win. Trey Townsend finished with 21 points for the Golden Grizzlies (6-7). ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
